-- Hong Kong Stocks Decline on China Curbs, Cyprus Concern
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B u r g o s
-- 2013-03-26T01:37:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-26/hong-kong-stocks-decline-on-china-curbs-cyprus-concern.html
Hong Kong  stocks  fell as Chinese
developers declined after a newspaper reported lenders are
capping lending to the property sector and companies getting
revenue from Europe fell.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  slid 0.3 percent to 22,194.66 as of
9:37 a.m. in Hong Kong. The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index
dropped 0.3 percent to 10,942.82.  To contact the reporter on this story:
